RELEASE OF ALL CLAIMS
This Release arises out of, and reference is hereby made to, the lawsuit pending
in the Superior Court of the State of California, County of Los Angeles, bearing Case
Number 20STCV36044 and entitled Laura Alcaraz, et al v. L.A.C.M.T.A.
The Undersigned, being of lawful age, for the sole consideration of $9,000.00 to
the Undersigned on behalf of myself and my heirs, administrators, executors, successors
and assigns, hereby releases, acquits and forever discharges Los Angeles County
Metropolitan Transportation Authority, Victor Castro and all of the agents, servants,
successors, heirs, executors, associations, partnerships and affiliated companies or
entities thereof, of and from any and all claims, actions, causes of action, demands, rights,
damages, costs, loss of service, expenses and compensation whatsoever which the
Undersigned now has or which may hereafter accrue on account of or in any way arising
out of any and all known and unknown, foreseen and unforeseen bodily and personal
injuries, property damage, and the consequences thereof resulting from the alleged
incident or events which occurred on or about October 8, 2019, at Foothill and Bledsoe
in Sun Valley, California.
It is understood and agreed that this settlement is the compromise of a disputed
claim, and that the payment made pursuant to this settlement is not to be construed as
an admission of liability on the part of the party or parties hereby released, and that said
party or parties deny liability and merely seek to avoid litigation and buy their peace.
